unit.comment: /* When #included in pcre2test, we don't need the table of digit sets, nor the the large main UCD tables. */
/* This vector is a list of lists of scripts for the Script Extension property. Each sublist is zero-terminated. */

/* These are the main two-stage UCD tables. The fields in each record are: script (8 bits), character type (8 bits), grapheme break property (8 bits), offset to multichar other cases or zero (8 bits), offset to other case or zero (32 bits, signed), script extension (16 bits, signed), and a dummy 16-bit field to make the whole thing a multiple of 4 bytes. */
